Defines the backlog data model: a `Vec<Task>` pairing stable task ids with the shared `ctx-core::status_table::Row` fields (task description, impact, difficulty), plus the fixed three-value vocabularies and priority-sort logic.

Each `Task` carries an id assigned once at migration/`add-task` time; id `0` is a placeholder for pre-migration rows and must be backfilled before persisting. `backfill_ids(store)` assigns sequential ids starting from `max(existing ids) + 1`, skipping any id already present, and is idempotent — calling it twice on the same store is safe.

Impact and difficulty are case-insensitive enums: `["high", "medium", "low"]` and `["easy", "medium", "hard"]` respectively. `normalize_impact()` and `normalize_difficulty()` validate and return the lowercase canonical form, or error with `StatusError::BadImpact`/`BadDifficulty`. The `rank()` helper never panics — unknown values sort past the end of their vocabulary, so hand-edited files with typos don't crash.

`priority_sorted(store) -> Vec<Task>` returns a copy sorted by impact (high first), then difficulty (easy first) within an impact band, stable on insertion order for ties. The store's own insertion order is never mutated.